.
 W
\series medium 
e 
\series default 
see
\series medium 
 that the
\series default 
 microscopic
\series medium 
 force on the tip 
\series default 
is given as
\series medium 
 the 
\series default 
sum of the 
\emph on 
partial forces
\series medium 
\emph default 
 on 
\series default 
\emph on 
all
\series medium 
\emph default 
 atoms of the tip due to all of the atoms in the surface
\series default 
.
 
\layout Standard


\series medium 
The above expression does not require that the system is in equilibrium,
 and
\series default 
, due to partitioning of the total Hamiltonian discussed above, Eq.
 (
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{Hamiltonian}

\end_inset 

), it naturally tends to zero when the tip and the surface are separated.
 It
\series medium 
 is also equivalent to the 
\series default 
static
\series medium 
 definition 
