How to compile the code
\layout Standard
\added_space_bottom bigskip 
The code should be in the form of a gzipped tarball, such as 
\family typewriter 
scifi_3.51.tgz
\family default 
.
 Assuming this, then type:
\layout Standard
\added_space_bottom bigskip 

\family typewriter 
tar -zxvf scifi_3.51.tgz
\layout Standard
\noindent 
this will extract all the necessary files, including directories 
\family typewriter 
SHELLM 
\family default 
(the main code including the vAFM part) and
\family typewriter 
 IMAGE
\family default 
 (the image part of the code), a directory 
\family typewriter 
examples
\family default 
 containing three example input files and the corresponding output files.
 
\layout Standard

To compile the program, a 
\family typewriter 
Makefile
\family default 
 in either of the directories 
\family typewriter 
SHELLM
\family default 
 and
\family typewriter 
 IMAGE,
\family default 
 should be edited to include the command of your Fortran 77 or Fortran 90
 compiler (g77 is the default), along with any compiler options (-o (optimised)
 is default).
 
\layout Standard

The code can be compiled into either a serial execultable or a MPICH parallel
 version, via the 
\family typewriter 
cpp
\family default 
 precompiler.
 To compile a parallel version, the 
\family typewriter 
MPIFLAG = -DMPI 
\family default 
must be added to the 
\family typewriter 
Makefile
\family default 
, as well as the MPICH flags to your compiler and the path of your 
\family typewriter 
mpich.h
\family default 
 header file.
 
\layout Standard
\added_space_bottom smallskip 
To compile the code, type
\family typewriter 
 
\layout Standard
\added_space_bottom smallskip 

\family typewriter 
make
\family default 
 
\layout Standard
\noindent 
in either of the two directories; this will produce the executables
\family typewriter 
 shellm
\family default 
 and 
\family typewriter 
image
\family default 
, respectively.
 Make sure that you have access to both executables, i.e.
 that the directories are included in the 
\family typewriter 
$path
\family default 
 variable.
 
