If present, a xyz format file with all atomic coordinates after run finishes
 will be printed out.
 This will produce two files, 
\family typewriter 
\emph on 
name_core.xyz
\family default 
\emph default 
 and 
\family typewriter 
\emph on 
name_shll.xyz
\family default 
\emph default 
 containing the atomic and shell positions, respectively.
 
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Options
\emph default 
:
\series bold 
 
\series default 
none
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Default
\emph default 
: off
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Example
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
xyz 
