\layout Subsubsection*

update_RST
\layout Standard
\noindent 
If present, this flag will activate an update of the atomic positions in
 the RST file after every relaxation step if minimising energy, and will
 update atomic positions and velocities after every 
\family typewriter 
\size footnotesize 
i_saved_RST
\family default 
\size default 
 timesteps (given in 
\family typewriter 
param.inc
\family default 
 file) during an MD run.
 This will slow down the code; however, it will save you the latest geometry
 in the case of a crash or if you want to kill a running job.
\layout Standard
\noindent 
Options: none
\layout Standard
\noindent 
Default: off
\layout Standard
\noindent 
Example: 
\series bold 
update_RST
\layout Subsubsection

Geometry optimisation options
\begin_inset LatexCommand \label{Sec::Geometry-optimisation-options}

\end_inset 


\layout Subsubsection*
\noindent 
max_opt
\layout Standard
\noindent 
Maximum number of relaxation iterations (N) to be used within the optimisation
 method chosen (see below).
 
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Options
\emph default 
: N
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Default
\emph default 
: N =
\series bold 
 100
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Example
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
max_opt 15
\layout Subsubsection*
\noindent 
optim
\layout Standard
\noindent 
The energy minimisation which is specified using this keyword is the default
 algorithm.
 Note that if the 
\family typewriter 
.<MDcontrol>
\family default 
 box is found (section 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{Sec::MDcontrol-Box}

\end_inset 

), then the Molecular Dynamic simulation is performed in which case this
 option is either ignored when fictious dynamics with shells is assumed,
 or used to optimise shells positions in the case of the only-cores dynamics
 (more details in section 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{Sec::MDcontrol-Box}

\end_inset 

).
\layout Standard
\noindent 
