This option allows the frozen atoms of the tip to be moved during the MD
 or energy relaxation simulations.
 This option is implemented differently in either case.
\layout Subsubsection

During MD
\layout Standard

A single string command is used to specify the tip movement during the scan:
\layout Subsubsection*

howto 
\begin_inset Formula $A\,\,\, T\,\,\, v_{x}\,\,\, v_{y}$
\end_inset 


\layout Standard

The tip can be scanned laterally at a constant velocity, or oscillated sinusoida
lly in the z-direction, or both at the same time.
 The option is followed by four parameters, as indicated above, which control
 the movement of the tip, according to the following equations of motion:
\layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula \[
x=x_{0}+v_{x}n\Delta t\]

\end_inset 


\layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula \[
y=y_{0}+v_{y}n\Delta t\]

\end_inset 


\layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula \[
z=z_{0}+A\sin\left(\frac{2\pi n\Delta t}{T}\right)\]

\end_inset 

where 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset 

 is the timestep number and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta t$
\end_inset 

 is the timestep itself.
 
\series medium 
The units of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset 

 are Å, the units of 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset 

 are ps, the units of 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{x}$
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{y}$
\end_inset 

 Å/ps.
 
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Options
\series medium 
\emph default 
: 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset 

 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset 

 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{x}$
\end_inset 

 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{y}$
\end_inset 


\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Default
\series medium 
\emph default 
: no
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Example
\series medium 
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
howto
\series medium 
 4.0 20.0 1.0 1.0
