\begin_inset Formula $\Delta f$
\end_inset 

 could be maintained aproximately constant close to the set value,
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta f$
\end_inset 

 (real);
\layout Itemize

if OFF, then the distance is kept exactly constant instead (constant height
 mode); the frequency will change along the simulation, still kept at resonance;
\end_deeper 
\layout Itemize

AGC is ON/OFF (logical):
\begin_deeper 
\layout Itemize

if ON, then gain control allows to keep the oscillation amplitude approximately
 constant close to the set value, 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset 

 (real), by constantly adjusting the excitation amplitude;
